The en:foo link is an indicator that items with this metadata should be considered for linking from the en article linked to and that potentially the metadata in the article (esp titles, composers, and performers) should link to that enwiki article.

The regular link indicates objects with this metadata should be considered for inclusion in commons gallery Foo and Bar.

Fixme is a tag to mark items with that metadata should be marked for manual inspection for the given reason.

If you think of other things we might want to do in response to metadata, just let me know... the software to read this is not written yet, so anything is possible. :) If you need/want to see complete metadata for an item which uses one of these tags, please let me know.

Don't change the stuff before the ->
